      "text": "All LibraVox recordings are in the public domain.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-002",
      "start": 6.04,
      "end": 11.16,
      "text": "For more information, or to volunteer, please visit LibraVox.org.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-003",
      "start": 11.8,
      "end": 15.78,
      "text": "Recorded by Christine Doer, the known as Assa, Florida.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-004",
      "start": 17.42,
      "end": 20.78,
      "text": "Esaups Fables, the Peacock, and Juno.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-005",
      "start": 22.44,
      "end": 27.42,
      "text": "The Peacock was greatly discontented because he had not a beautiful voice like the Night",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-006",
      "start": 27.42,
      "end": 31.06,
      "text": "and Gail, and he went and complained to Juno about it.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-007",
      "start": 31.9,
      "end": 35.68,
      "text": "The Night and Gail song, he said, is the envy of all the birds.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-008",
      "start": 36.6,
      "end": 40.2,
      "text": "But whenever I utter a sound, I become a laughingstock.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-009",
      "start": 41.26,
      "end": 46.88,
      "text": "The goddess tried to console him by saying, You have not, it is true, the power of song.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-010",
      "start": 47.74,
      "end": 50.48,
      "text": "But then you far excel all the rest in beauty.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-011",
      "start": 51.48,
      "end": 56.14,
      "text": "Your neck flashes like the emerald, and your splendid tail is a marvel of gorgeous",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-012",
      "start": 56.14,
      "end": 56.74,
      "text": "color.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-013",
      "start": 57.48,
      "end": 59.56,
      "text": "But the Peacock was not appeased.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-014",
      "start": 60.04,
      "end": 63.58,
      "text": "What is the use, he said, of being beautiful with a voice like mine?",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-015",
      "start": 64.72,
      "end": 68.72,
      "text": "Then Juno replied, with a shade of sternness in her tones.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-016",
      "start": 69.52,
      "end": 72.68,
      "text": "Fate has allotted to all their destined gifts.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-017",
      "start": 72.68,
      "end": 80.94,
      "text": "To yourself beauty, to the eagle strength, to the Night and Gail song, and so on to all",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-018",
      "start": 80.94,
      "end": 82.24,
      "text": "the rest in their degree.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-019",
      "start": 83.2,
      "end": 86.0,
      "text": "But you alone are dissatisfied with your portion.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-020",
      "start": 86.96,
      "end": 93.14,
      "text": "Make then no more complaints, for if your present wish were granted, you would quickly",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-021",
      "start": 93.14,
      "end": 95.58,
      "text": "find cause for fresh discontent.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-022",
      "start": 98.2,
      "end": 99.96,
      "text": "End of the Peacock and Juno",
      "note": ""
    }
  ],
